{
  "text": "Currently, the layout of the input is such that the topology cannot be graphically manipulated. What is needed is an easier way to manipulate the topology of a reaction network, and this is a subject of current work [CITATION_1] . In that the simulator KINSOLVER is setup to execute many reaction networks at once, more flexibility in the output interface is desirable to display ensembles of models [CITATION_2] .",
